<HL>
   Sony Has Lighter Camcorder
</HL>
<DATE>
05/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   SNE
</CO>
<IN>
HOME ELECTRONICS, FURNISHINGS, APPLIANCES (HMF)
</IN>
<LP>
   TOKYO -- Sony Corp. introduced what it claims is the
lightest and smallest camcorder on the market.
   Sony said its new TR-45 model weighs 690 grams, or about 1
1/2 pounds. The company said it trimmed 100 grams from the
weight of its popular TR-55, introduced last summer, by
developing a smaller image sensor and lens, and by reducing
the weight of other parts.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The fully automatic TR-45 goes on sale in Japan on July 1
for 130,000 yen ($868), Sony officials said. It will be
introduced in the U.S. later in the summer and in Europe in
the fall, they said.
   Introduction of the compact TR-55 last year greatly
boosted world-wide demand for 8mm camcorders, and Sony
officials said they expect to sell more than three million
8mm machines this year.
</TEXT>
