   StatesWest Airlines Orders Jets
</HL>
<DATE>
05/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C21
</SO>
<CO>
   SWAL BA
</CO>
<LP>
   PHOENIX, Ariz. -- StatesWest Airlines said it ordered four
Boeing Dash 8-100 regional prop jets plus spare engines and
parts for $45 million from Boeing Canada Ltd., a unit of
Seattle-based Boeing Co.
   StatesWest, a regional airline that flies to destinations
in Arizona and California, said it also acquired options for
an additional four Dash 8-100 prop jets. StatesWest said it
expects the first four planes to be delivered over the next
nine months.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The Boeing Dash 8-100 carries 37 passengers.
