   Eurotunnel is trying to arrange a #2.5 billion ($4.22
billion) expansion of the credits and equity funds available
to it to cover an increase in the estimated cost of
completing the project. The new funds would increase
Eurotunnel's funds to about #8.5 billion from #6 billion.
