<HL>
   International Brief -- ABB Asea Brown Boveri AG:
   Earnings Before Taxes Rose
   47% in the First Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/30/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9
</SO>
<CO>
   ASEAY S.ABB
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   ABB Asea Brown Boveri AG, the big Swiss and Swedish
electrical engineering company, reported that its earnings
before taxes in the first quarter rose 47% to $239 million
from $163 million a year earlier.
   The company said operating earnings after depreciation
rose 45% to $333 million from $229 million a year earlier.
Earnings after financial items rose 25% to $215 million.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   First-quarter sales rose 39% to $6.11 billion from $4.40
billion a year earlier. When acquisitions, divestitures and
exchange-rate changes are excluded, sales rose 9% in the
period, the company said.
   The company cited good earnings growth in the power
transmission, power distribution and financial services
segments.
</TEXT>
