<GV>
TREASURY DEPARTMENT (TRE)
</GV>
<LP>
   WASHINGTON -- The Treasury plans to raise $1.15 billion in
new cash with the sale Monday of a record $17.2 billion in
short-term bills to redeem $16.06 billion in maturing bills.
   The offering will be divided evenly between 13-week and
26-week bills maturing on Sept. 6 and Dec. 6, respectively.
They will be available in minimum denominations of $10,000.
</LP>
